Meet <b>Nicci</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Nicci lives at <a href='/home/?user=bibsy'>30046 Lakewood</a>, which is located along the beautiful windswept shore in Lakeview.  She's enjoyed going for long jogs on the beach ever since moving to Millsberry on April 16, 2005.<br><br>Nicci is well known around <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/">Millsberry Academy</a> for her amazing intellect!  She loves science, and her favorite subjects in school are biology, chemistry, and computers.  Since classes have let out for the summer, Nicci is planning to spend a lot of time in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a>, examining plants and insects, and learning about Millsberry's biology on her own!  She also wants to use some of her free time this summer to build her own computer.  Nicci actually finds the logical problems that are a part of computer programming very fun and challenging, and she says that working with computers can be just as creative as drawing or painting.  Sometimes, Nicci will turn on her favorite classic rock, soft rock, or classical CD and work on her computer for hours on end.  <br><br>Nicci doesn't spend all of her time cooped up inside, however.  She's very athletic and has an impressive trophy collection to prove it.  Nicci often heads to the park or playground, where she'll play a pickup game of basketball with her friends or give her throwing arm a workout with a game of catch.  She's usually easy to spot on the field or basketball court, since Nicci is the one in the violet, light blue, and white jersey, hitting a string of three-point shots or reaching back to throw a long bomb.<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Nicci, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
